<p>In C#, if I have a polymorphic object, how can I determine the type of the object, with out checking for the base type?</p>  <p>Here is an example:</p>  <pre><code>class object1 : object2 {  }  testObject = new object1(); </code></pre>  <p>Both the following lines of code return true:</p>  <pre><code>bool test1 = testObject is object1; bool test2 = testObject is object2; </code></pre>  <p>How can I do a check so that <code>test2</code> returns false?</p>